claim.claim-text:
1. A portable messaging device, comprising:
a wireless receiver;
a processor coupled to the wireless receiver;
a velocity sensor communicatively coupled to the processor;
a memory coupled to the processor; the memory holding program instructions that when operated by the processor, cause the portable messaging device to automatically disable audible alert signaling for an incoming message in response to determining, based on information from the velocity sensor, that a current velocity of the portable messaging device exceeds a threshold.
